imdb.title: Sora no otoshimono
imdb.plot: Girl-crazy Tomoki's quiet life gets turned upside down when beautiful, winged Ikaros falls from the sky -- and starts calling him master.

episodes.title: Kimi mo Nuge! Kaette Kita Yusha
episodes.plot: Tomoki has another strange dream. Baffled at the meaning, Nymph suggests diving into Tomoki's dream. Everyone's dreams besides Tomoki's are visited. So what is Tomoki dream really about?

episodes.title: Kyougaku ! tenshi wa kyonyuu datta !!
episodes.plot: Tomoki struggles to maintain control of his libido and retreats to a temple to control his desires.

episodes.title: A Fight with Pride!
episodes.plot: Tomoki enters a wrestling tournament, using the opportunity to fulfil his lustful desires.

episodes.title: To the Death! The Bath Battle at -1.4°C!
episodes.plot: Mikako organizes a snowball fight between the boys and girls. Tomoki and Mikako are made commanders. The objective is too wipe out the enemy's commander. What could possibly go wrong?

episodes.title: A Friend and a Super-Sibling from the Heavens
episodes.plot: Sugata and Sohara use Nymph's Dive Game program to travel to the Synapse. In the process Sohara causes an item to fall to earth. Tomoki uses the item to build a transforming 'panty' robot pedal bicycle.

episodes.title: Reach a Decision! The Up and Down of Heaven and Hell
episodes.plot: After Tomoki learns that the girls at school find him undesirable and unintelligent, the gang takes part in a quiz to find out just how smart they really are. Meanwhile, in Synapse, a plan to destroy Ikaros and Nymph is taking shape!

episodes.title: Eating Watermelon Tomoki
episodes.plot: Even though they know it's a risky move, Astraea and Nymph decide to raid Ikaros's watermelon patch. Meanwhile, Sugata and Nymph find themselves in serious danger after infiltrating Synapse.

episodes.title: The Song of the Angels Echoes in the Sky
episodes.plot: The time has arrived for Astraea to make a choice. Will she do the Sky Master's bidding and destroy Ikaros and Nymph once and for all? Or will she listen to Tomoki and find the strength to choose her own destiny?

episodes.title: Shoot Out! Fishing at the Jumbo Carnival of Dreams
episodes.plot: During the Summer Festival, Mikako organizes a fishing contest at the swimming pool. There's only one way to win: reel in the curviest catch! Later, Ikaros tries to find the best way to spend her allowance.

episodes.title: Peek Into the Fantasy Field
episodes.plot: Sohara teaches Ikaros about the ins and outs of marriage. Meanwhile, Tomoki puts the final touches on his summer project: a massive network of periscope-like tubing that allows him to sneak a peek at girls all over town!

episodes.title: The Edge of an Indiscriminate Requiem
episodes.plot: Tomoki takes action when Ikaros, Nymph, and Astraea are overpowered in battle against Chaos! After the fight ends, it looks like peaceful days are ahead - until it becomes obvious that Ikaros still faces a serious crisis.

episodes.title: Forte Wings Soaring for Tomorrow
episodes.plot: Tomoki makes a splash with the girls in swim class when he transforms into pool water. Later, the whole gang heads to a wedding - but who will be walking down the aisle?

episodes.title: Yûsha sekai ni tatsu!
episodes.plot: All Tomoki wants is peace and quiet, but after having continuous dreams of an angel talking to him, his friend Sohara suggests a visit to Eishiro Sugata. Sugata tells them about a dark hole and they all set out to find its location.

episodes.title: An Airborne Prismatic Panty Adventure
episodes.plot: Tomoki's got one of Ikaros's cards in his possession when he accidentally catches a glimpse of Sohara's panties! The card's power activates, and now there's nothing Sohara can do to keep her panties from flying away!

episodes.title: Angeloid Directive Zero
episodes.plot: Ikaros seems to lack some basic computing skills, so Sugata urges Tomoki to assign the Angeloid various tasks in order to learn her strengths and weaknesses. One of her flaws is pretty obvious: she doesn't know how to have fun.

episodes.title: Love and Triangles, Revisited
episodes.plot: After Sohara uses one of Ikaros's cards to make a wish, Tomoki finds himself in an explosive situation: Every time he looks at a pair of panties, the bloomers go boom!

episodes.title: Hot Night with the Big Fish
episodes.plot: During a visit to Mikako's house, Tomoki ends up on the run from gun-toting gangsters. He manages to escape - and quickly finds himself stranded on a deserted island and stalked by a horrifying monster!

episodes.title: Swimsuit Surf Brigade, Go!Go!Go!
episodes.plot: After the surprising arrival of a new Angeloid named Nymph, the gang heads to the beach! Nymph seems to have a bit of an attitude, but she's still willing to help when Sohara's lack of swimming skills puts her in a serious situation.

episodes.title: The Brainy, Heart-Pounding Transfer Students
episodes.plot: Ikaros and Nymph make quite a splash when they enroll at Tomoki's school. Later, mysterious new questions arise when Nymph discovers a shocking secret about Ikaros's past.

episodes.title: For Whom the Shooting Festival is Held
episodes.plot: A local festival turns into a cork gun shootout, and there's $100,000 prize for the last person standing. Later, after Nymph reveals her purpose for being on Earth, Ikaros finds herself on the edge of reverting to her former self.

episodes.title: The Delusional Story That Began with a Lie
episodes.plot: Ikaros starts lying to her friends in an effort to act more human. Meanwhile, after Tomoki starts a business in order to raise funds for a saucy DVD, Nymph turns his life upside down by making him irresistible to women!

episodes.title: Where the Melodious Words of an Angel Go
episodes.plot: It's a musical showdown at the Cultural Fair! Ikaros is the star of the show when Tomoki and the gang put a band together and take on the classical orchestra of the nearby private academy!

episodes.title: Off We Go to My Bathouse Paradise
episodes.plot: Tomoki's on a mission to sneak into the girls' bathing area. With Sugata's assistance (and one of Ikaros's cards) he devises the perfect disguise to accomplish his goal: he transforms into a cute girl!

episodes.title: Chains of No Escape
episodes.plot: No matter how hard their friends try to help, Ikaros and Nymph just can't seem to crack a smile. After the Angeloids decide to work on the problem together, they take Tomoki out on the town for a three-way date!

episodes.title: Queen of the Sky
episodes.plot: After surprising Tomoki with a sudden farewell, Ikaros endures a treacherous encounter with Harpy and Gamma. If Ikaros can find a way to defeat them, she may finally break her chains and find the happiness she desires.

episodes.title: Project Pink
episodes.plot: The gang heads to a water park, and Tomoki goes undercover to feast his eyes on as much flesh as he can. When his peeping plan falls apart, Nymph punishes him - even though she secretly wants him to be her new master!
